12/06/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Minister for European Integration Neven Mimica and Serbian Deputy Prime Minister Cedomir Jovanovic met on Wednesday (11 June), announcing afterwards that their countries are ready to intensify bilateral co-operation and exchange experiences about the process of EU integration. During a joint news conference after the talks, they said strengthened ties would contribute to the stabilisation and prosperity of the whole region. Jovanovic added that Belgrade was seriously considering withdrawing Serbian Army troops from the border with Croatia. Zagreb has made that one of the conditions for lifting its visa regime for Serbia-Montenegro citizens. (Blic - 12/06/03; Croatian Radio, HINA, BBC - 11/06/03)
